1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,200
Let's eat.

2
00:00:01,413 --> 00:00:02,568
Let's go.

3
00:00:02,569 --> 00:00:04,937
- Let's go eat.
- Let's eat.

4
00:00:05,939 --> 00:00:07,072
Let's go.

5
00:00:09,543 --> 00:00:11,077
(Yu Jun keeps going straight.)

6
00:00:11,078 --> 00:00:12,545
- No.
- This way.

7
00:00:12,813 --> 00:00:14,380
- You can't go in there.
- You can't go in.

8
00:00:14,548 --> 00:00:15,548
No.

9
00:00:15,549 --> 00:00:16,549
You must be confused.

10
00:00:16,717 --> 00:00:17,884
You can't go in.

11
00:00:17,885 --> 00:00:20,086
You should get used to not going in there.

12
00:00:20,087 --> 00:00:21,120
That looks good.

13
00:00:21,321 --> 00:00:22,249
Let's order here.
(They arrive at the restaurant.)

14
00:00:23,223 --> 00:00:24,523
(Carefully choosing)

15
00:00:24,524 --> 00:00:25,491
There's jjajangmyeon too?

16
00:00:25,492 --> 00:00:26,625
Can I order two?

17
00:00:26,626 --> 00:00:27,860
- I ordered one.
- Can I order two?

18
00:00:27,861 --> 00:00:28,628
Eat mine later.

19
00:00:28,629 --> 00:00:29,928
(TOMORROW BY TOGETHER has
a hearty appetite.)

20
00:00:30,397 --> 00:00:32,631
(Babbling)

21
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:34,300
Yu Jun is talkative now.

22
00:00:34,301 --> 00:00:35,502
(He babbles as the uncles are talking.)

23
00:00:36,336 --> 00:00:37,336
Did you order tteokbokki?

24
00:00:37,337 --> 00:00:39,371
- Did you order it?
- Is this what you ordered?

25
00:00:39,372 --> 00:00:41,407
- Seasoned...
- I'll order one more seaweed soup.

26
00:00:41,408 --> 00:00:42,241
It's up there.

27
00:00:42,609 --> 00:00:43,943
No. Let's order one more.

28
00:00:44,144 --> 00:00:45,845
- Are we ordering two seaweed soups?
- Tteokbokki.

29
00:00:46,613 --> 00:00:48,280
Anyone else who wants to order?

30
00:00:48,281 --> 00:00:50,149
- We're done.
- "Select" and "delete."

31
00:00:50,918 --> 00:00:51,818
Yu Jun, try pushing it.

32
00:00:54,154 --> 00:00:55,181
What is Yu Jun going to eat?

33
00:00:55,182 --> 00:00:56,322
(If you're done ordering, follow me.)

34
00:00:57,124 --> 00:00:58,524
- We have his food.
- He has food.

35
00:00:58,525 --> 00:00:59,725
(A new student heading to magic school.)

36
00:00:59,726 --> 00:01:01,994
Yu Jun, let's go sit over there
in the back.

37
00:01:02,663 --> 00:01:04,363
Yu Jun, let's sit here.

38
00:01:04,932 --> 00:01:06,232
Should I bring that?

39
00:01:06,233 --> 00:01:07,367
Is there a baby chair here?

40
00:01:07,368 --> 00:01:08,234
- There is.
- Is there?

41
00:01:09,903 --> 00:01:12,438
(Yu Jun, let's sit in a chair.)

42
00:01:12,439 --> 00:01:13,472
You're here.

43
00:01:13,473 --> 00:01:15,207
(That's water.)

44
00:01:16,777 --> 00:01:19,345
- I hope their food is good.
- Just pour it in.

45
00:01:19,638 --> 00:01:21,220
(Abalone baby food
and Korean beef seaweed soup)

46
00:01:21,221 --> 00:01:22,481
Seaweed soup for kids. That's cute.

47
00:01:23,003 --> 00:01:23,916
Oh, dear.

48
00:01:24,151 --> 00:01:25,051
(The seaweed soup looks good.)

49
00:01:25,052 --> 00:01:26,352
Yu Jun's food looks great.

50
00:01:27,354 --> 00:01:28,321
Yu Jun, open your mouth.

51
00:01:29,456 --> 00:01:31,991
(His first attempt
at feeding Yu Jun seaweed soup)

52
00:01:32,259 --> 00:01:33,993
How do I feed him soup?

53
00:01:36,096 --> 00:01:37,696
(Now I'll have some rice.)

54
00:01:37,798 --> 00:01:38,998
He's good at scooping now.

55
00:01:40,033 --> 00:01:42,334
I don't have to feed him anymore.
He can scoop.

56
00:01:44,505 --> 00:01:48,374
(Look at me. I can eat alone now.)

57
00:01:48,642 --> 00:01:50,076
Let's finish our food first.

58
00:01:50,244 --> 00:01:52,812
Let's eat and think about it later.

59
00:01:52,813 --> 00:01:54,814
I'll just eat fast first.

60
00:01:54,815 --> 00:01:55,782
Okay.

61
00:01:56,017 --> 00:01:57,650
I'll eat really fast too.

62
00:01:57,918 --> 00:01:59,652
- Gosh. That's so much food.
- I know.

63
00:02:00,220 --> 00:02:02,121
(Surprised to see a bigger portion
than he expected)

64
00:02:02,489 --> 00:02:03,856
(Let me feed Yu Jun first.)

65
00:02:03,857 --> 00:02:04,890
Let's eat.

66
00:02:05,425 --> 00:02:06,658
SOOBIN, why don't you eat first?

67
00:02:06,994 --> 00:02:08,061
Okay.

68
00:02:08,262 --> 00:02:09,195
Let's put his bib on.

69
00:02:09,496 --> 00:02:12,364
(Now they naturally put a bib on Yu Jun.)

70
00:02:15,068 --> 00:02:15,934
He's enjoying it.

71
00:02:16,169 --> 00:02:17,336
Yes. He can eat well alone.

72
00:02:18,539 --> 00:02:19,939
Yu Jun is all grown up.

73
00:02:21,642 --> 00:02:22,408
Open your mouth.

74
00:02:22,409 --> 00:02:24,110
(Let me really enjoy my food
now that I have a bib on.)

75
00:02:26,380 --> 00:02:27,914
It's too hot.

76
00:02:27,941 --> 00:02:28,708
(Give me more.)
Open your mouth.

77
00:02:29,816 --> 00:02:32,184
(He opens his mouth as he feeds Yu Jun.)

78
00:02:33,153 --> 00:02:36,021
(Big eaters TOMORROW BY TOGETHER are
eating fast without talking.)

79
00:02:36,189 --> 00:02:38,490
(I can't be left out!)

80
00:02:38,491 --> 00:02:41,126
(Yu Jun takes a bite,
and the uncle takes a bite.)

81
00:02:42,062 --> 00:02:43,996
(Seaweed soup, pork cutlet, jjajangmyeon,
udon, mushroom soup, fried chicken,)

82
00:02:43,997 --> 00:02:45,177
(and much more...)

83
00:02:45,178 --> 00:02:46,198
The bib isn't doing any good.

84
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:47,800
Didn't we order more?

85
00:02:49,770 --> 00:02:52,071
(This is what I'm talking about.)

86
00:02:53,640 --> 00:02:57,009
(The uncles have ramyeon as always.)

87
00:02:57,010 --> 00:02:57,943
The fried chicken is good.

88
00:02:58,312 --> 00:02:59,145
Is that so?

89
00:02:59,213 --> 00:03:02,081
(Then let me try some.)

90
00:03:02,783 --> 00:03:05,285
(I heard the fried chicken is good.)

91
00:03:05,452 --> 00:03:06,452
Is the tteokbokki good?

92
00:03:06,453 --> 00:03:07,420
- It is.
- It's so good.

93
00:03:07,421 --> 00:03:09,255
- The fried chicken is good.
- The fried chicken is...

94
00:03:09,256 --> 00:03:10,656
The breading is really good.

95
00:03:10,936 --> 00:03:12,425
He's really enjoying his food.

96
00:03:16,263 --> 00:03:18,231
Yu Jun.

97
00:03:22,135 --> 00:03:23,669
(I got some food on my hand.)

98
00:03:24,237 --> 00:03:26,538
(SOOBIN is busy feeding him
and wiping his hands.)

99
00:03:26,539 --> 00:03:27,573
Yu Jun, is it good?

100
00:03:27,574 --> 00:03:29,007
You're eating well.

101
00:03:29,309 --> 00:03:31,443
(He might even eat the fork.)

102
00:03:32,879 --> 00:03:34,579
Why do you keep doing that pose?

103
00:03:35,175 --> 00:03:36,742
- HUENINGKAI, do you want to feed him?
- Sure.

104
00:03:37,351 --> 00:03:39,953
He's doing so well eating on his own.

105
00:03:40,487 --> 00:03:41,320
He's tough.

106
00:03:42,089 --> 00:03:43,356
(Yu Jun eats a big scoop.)

107
00:03:43,357 --> 00:03:44,924
Yu Jun, you're loving your food.

108
00:03:45,392 --> 00:03:47,093
He's doing a good job feeding himself.

109
00:03:47,628 --> 00:03:50,196
You eat one bite,
and I'll feed you one bite.

110
00:03:50,631 --> 00:03:53,499
There you go. Good job.

111
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:55,368
(It's my turn now.)

112
00:03:55,636 --> 00:03:56,636
Open your mouth.

113
00:03:56,637 --> 00:03:58,004
- Dried radish salad.
- Good job.

114
00:03:58,505 --> 00:04:01,373
(Here comes a food plane.)

115
00:04:01,374 --> 00:04:03,676
- Good job.
- You're eating well.

116
00:04:03,710 --> 00:04:04,977
He's happy.

117
00:04:06,046 --> 00:04:07,013
- He's cute.
- That's good.

118
00:04:07,214 --> 00:04:08,114
That's cute.

119
00:04:08,115 --> 00:04:09,182
(Watching him eat makes us full.)

120
00:04:09,469 --> 00:04:10,315
Choi Yu Jun.

121
00:04:10,751 --> 00:04:12,318
Who do you get your good looks from?

122
00:04:12,452 --> 00:04:13,285
I know.

123
00:04:13,286 --> 00:04:14,353
Do you get it from me?

124
00:04:14,755 --> 00:04:16,489
(I got my big appetite from you.)

125
00:04:16,524 --> 00:04:17,557
I guess it's from me.

126
00:04:17,558 --> 00:04:19,258
(Swaying his leg in agreement)

127
00:04:20,093 --> 00:04:20,826
Yu Jun...

128
00:04:20,827 --> 00:04:22,695
- He's happy.
- He's really happy.

129
00:04:22,696 --> 00:04:24,229
- He's so happy.
- He's got a lot of teeth coming in.

130
00:04:24,765 --> 00:04:26,599
(He's so happy,
he starts playing with his seaweed soup.)

131
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:27,501
Oh, my.

132
00:04:27,502 --> 00:04:29,469
- He's playing with his seaweed soup.
- He's playing with his food.

133
00:04:29,470 --> 00:04:31,738
Let's give him one more bite
and take his bib off.

134
00:04:32,239 --> 00:04:33,539
- He ate a lot.
- Yes.

135
00:04:34,541 --> 00:04:37,710
(This is the last bite.)

136
00:04:38,078 --> 00:04:39,979
- Good job.
- You're done.

137
00:04:39,980 --> 00:04:41,480
- The way he's moving his mouth...
- You're done now.

138
00:04:41,481 --> 00:04:43,716
doesn't look like he's full.

139
00:04:46,887 --> 00:04:47,753
Are you happy?

140
00:04:47,754 --> 00:04:49,455
He sticks out his upper lip
when he's happy.

141
00:04:49,456 --> 00:04:51,090
He pouts with his lower lip
when he's upset.

142
00:04:51,191 --> 00:04:52,391
(My lips?)

143
00:04:52,392 --> 00:04:53,359
That's true.

144
00:04:53,794 --> 00:04:55,495
His upper lip is covering
his lower lip now...

145
00:04:55,496 --> 00:04:56,529
because he's so happy.

146
00:04:58,031 --> 00:04:59,465
- Are you all full?
- Yes.

147
00:04:59,866 --> 00:05:00,999
I'm not full yet.

148
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:03,135
- You eat.
- Take your time.

149
00:05:03,136 --> 00:05:05,504
(Yu Jun cleans his table.)

150
00:05:05,505 --> 00:05:06,572
Have some fried chicken.

151
00:05:07,374 --> 00:05:09,809
(Wiping his chair)

152
00:05:10,677 --> 00:05:12,645
- We had tteokbokki too?
- Yes.

153
00:05:12,646 --> 00:05:14,046
You guys didn't tell me.

154
00:05:15,048 --> 00:05:16,181
Is this my reward for working hard?

155
00:05:16,182 --> 00:05:17,483
(Did I wipe it well?)

156
00:05:18,452 --> 00:05:20,052
(I feel great!)

157
00:05:20,053 --> 00:05:22,321
He got possessed!

158
00:05:22,322 --> 00:05:23,423
"I'm so happy!"

159
00:05:23,424 --> 00:05:24,824
(Shaking his head)

160
00:05:25,926 --> 00:05:27,260
(We're happy when you're happy.)

161
00:05:27,261 --> 00:05:28,794
Why is he looking up, though?

162
00:05:30,297 --> 00:05:31,631
The tteokbokki is really spicy.

163
00:05:31,898 --> 00:05:32,731
- What?
- What?

164
00:05:33,233 --> 00:05:35,267
- Shall we start cleaning up?
- Yes.

165
00:05:35,268 --> 00:05:37,336
(Playing with Yu Jun
after a quick cleanup)

166
00:05:40,307 --> 00:05:42,141
- He's possessed.
- It's intense.

167
00:05:43,610 --> 00:05:46,812
(YEONJUN challenges Yu Jun
to a head-shaking contest.)

168
00:05:47,414 --> 00:05:49,515
(I'm better!)

169
00:05:49,816 --> 00:05:50,783
He's suddenly excited.

170
00:05:50,917 --> 00:05:51,817
He likes it.

171
00:05:52,152 --> 00:05:53,419
(One more time!)

172
00:05:55,956 --> 00:05:58,925
(The 16-month-old has never seen
bleached hair shaking before.)

173
00:06:05,065 --> 00:06:07,933
(Shaking his head on the other side)

174
00:06:13,507 --> 00:06:14,640
Yu Jun, are you happy?

175
00:06:14,641 --> 00:06:15,641
Put it here.

176
00:06:15,842 --> 00:06:17,309
Give us a heart, then.

177
00:06:18,078 --> 00:06:19,979
(I love you.)

178
00:06:19,980 --> 00:06:22,148
- He does that when he's super happy.
- He's in a great mood.

179
00:06:22,482 --> 00:06:23,916
He does that
only when he's in a good mood.

180
00:06:24,151 --> 00:06:25,351
Yu Jun, wink.

181
00:06:25,986 --> 00:06:27,119
(Winking)

182
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:28,120
Yu Jun, wink.

183
00:06:28,121 --> 00:06:29,255
That's his wink.

184
00:06:30,257 --> 00:06:31,157
Yu Jun.

185
00:06:31,658 --> 00:06:33,092
Shall we go outside for a bit?

186
00:06:35,729 --> 00:06:39,198
(While they're cleaning up,
TAEHYUN goes outside with Yu Jun.)

187
00:06:46,740 --> 00:06:47,640
Hello.

188
00:06:48,875 --> 00:06:50,108
Yu Jun, this is too hot for you.

189
00:06:51,111 --> 00:06:52,178
You can't do it.

190
00:06:53,814 --> 00:06:55,815
(Holding tightly)

191
00:06:58,618 --> 00:07:00,819
(Rubbing his cheek)

192
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:06,992
(The two circles are on a date.)

193
00:07:08,195 --> 00:07:09,095
(Over there!)

194
00:07:09,096 --> 00:07:10,096
Do you want to go over there?

195
00:07:11,064 --> 00:07:14,700
(Let's go hang out with the uncles.)

196
00:07:17,404 --> 00:07:18,437
In 1, 2.

197
00:07:18,438 --> 00:07:20,406
(TAEHYUN and YEONJUN cheer.)

198
00:07:20,407 --> 00:07:21,674
(BEOMGYU laughs.)

199
00:07:21,675 --> 00:07:23,242
(Laughing louder)

200
00:07:23,243 --> 00:07:24,510
The toll reader.

201
00:07:24,845 --> 00:07:26,546
That's so adorable. Wait.

202
00:07:26,547 --> 00:07:28,147
Let me take a picture of him.

203
00:07:28,448 --> 00:07:30,115
- Do it.
- Let's do it again.

204
00:07:30,817 --> 00:07:32,651
(Cheering)

205
00:07:32,819 --> 00:07:34,720
- That's cute.
- He's shouting.

206
00:07:36,790 --> 00:07:38,557
Yu Jun, there are some older girls.

207
00:07:38,925 --> 00:07:40,692
He's shy.

208
00:07:40,693 --> 00:07:42,227
- He feels shy.
- He's shy.

209
00:07:42,228 --> 00:07:43,362
He's shy around the girls.

210
00:07:44,297 --> 00:07:45,397
(A stranger)

211
00:07:45,632 --> 00:07:46,498
Hey.

212
00:07:46,499 --> 00:07:47,967
- Bonk!
- Hey.

213
00:07:47,968 --> 00:07:50,329
(As Yu Jun tried to bump into a stranger,
they got flustered.)

214
00:07:50,330 --> 00:07:51,170
Hey, no.

215
00:07:51,438 --> 00:07:52,317
You can't do it to everyone.

216
00:07:52,318 --> 00:07:54,206
You can't try to crash into strangers.

217
00:07:55,342 --> 00:07:56,709
(Smiling)

218
00:07:57,383 --> 00:07:58,844
Shall we check Yu Jun's height?

219
00:07:58,912 --> 00:08:00,112
We can measure how tall he is.

220
00:08:00,113 --> 00:08:01,680
You're right. There's a scale too.

221
00:08:01,915 --> 00:08:02,815
Yu Jun.

222
00:08:03,416 --> 00:08:04,516
Get up here.

223
00:08:04,684 --> 00:08:06,218
- Are you shy?
- "I don't want to."

224
00:08:06,286 --> 00:08:07,353
Where are you going?

225
00:08:07,454 --> 00:08:08,354
Catch him.

226
00:08:09,122 --> 00:08:10,155
He wants to play on the stairs.

227
00:08:11,391 --> 00:08:12,858
Should we go up
and come back down right away?

228
00:08:12,859 --> 00:08:13,726
Okay.

229
00:08:13,894 --> 00:08:15,794
- Hold my hand.
- We can't do it many times.

230
00:08:16,062 --> 00:08:16,895
He's going up again?

231
00:08:16,896 --> 00:08:19,064
We'll just go up a few steps
and come back down.

232
00:08:21,368 --> 00:08:25,504
(Instead of Yu Jun,
HUENINGKAI checks his height.)

233
00:08:26,039 --> 00:08:27,106
Did I get taller?

234
00:08:27,307 --> 00:08:29,275
I think it's 183.5cm.

235
00:08:29,643 --> 00:08:30,476
What?

236
00:08:30,577 --> 00:08:32,645
- I think I'm 183cm.
- Let me help you.

237
00:08:32,946 --> 00:08:33,812
Stay.

238
00:08:34,314 --> 00:08:36,181
You did one step per foot.

239
00:08:37,517 --> 00:08:38,484
Your legs got longer.

240
00:08:38,952 --> 00:08:39,785
Let's go back down.

241
00:08:39,786 --> 00:08:42,087
Let's pick him up
and put him on the scale.

242
00:08:42,889 --> 00:08:43,789
- Okay.
- Great idea, right?

243
00:08:43,790 --> 00:08:45,023
- Okay.
- Yu Jun, here we go.

244
00:08:45,024 --> 00:08:46,525
In 1, 2, 3.

245
00:08:47,127 --> 00:08:49,395
(SOOBIN and TAEHYUN cheer.)

246
00:08:49,396 --> 00:08:51,764
(They keep cheering.)

247
00:08:51,765 --> 00:08:53,566
(Still cheering)

248
00:08:53,567 --> 00:08:55,367
- Get out of the way.
- Get out of the way.

249
00:08:55,368 --> 00:08:58,637
(They continued cheering.)

250
00:08:58,872 --> 00:08:59,639
All right, Yu Jun.

251
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:01,907
(He took the SOOBIN TAEHYUN Plane
to the scale.)

252
00:09:02,275 --> 00:09:03,275
Mom.

253
00:09:03,276 --> 00:09:04,610
Is it 11.4kg?

254
00:09:04,611 --> 00:09:07,512
- He doesn't weigh as much as I thought.
- Let's check his height.

255
00:09:07,513 --> 00:09:08,547
(Yu Jun doesn't cooperate.)

256
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:09,414
Yu Jun.

257
00:09:10,417 --> 00:09:11,650
Shall we measure it without the chart?

258
00:09:12,786 --> 00:09:13,886
Yu Jun, stay still.

259
00:09:14,955 --> 00:09:15,922
Here.

260
00:09:15,923 --> 00:09:17,156
(What is this?)

261
00:09:17,157 --> 00:09:19,191
Let's go with the average of you and me.

262
00:09:19,192 --> 00:09:20,192
(Yu Jun's height)

263
00:09:20,226 --> 00:09:21,726
But as you're moving...

264
00:09:21,727 --> 00:09:24,196
(Here's Yu Jun's height.)

265
00:09:24,331 --> 00:09:25,498
Are we around the same height?

266
00:09:25,999 --> 00:09:27,166
It's about here.

267
00:09:28,134 --> 00:09:29,101
Yu Jun.

268
00:09:29,102 --> 00:09:30,268
He hasn't grown any taller.

269
00:09:30,269 --> 00:09:31,436
He's 77cm.

270
00:09:31,671 --> 00:09:32,638
Why did he get shorter?

271
00:09:33,018 --> 00:09:35,441
He traveled back to the past.
He's Benjamin Button.

272
00:09:35,742 --> 00:09:36,642
Bonk!

273
00:09:38,545 --> 00:09:41,413
(I'm here to measure his height again.)

274
00:09:41,881 --> 00:09:43,381
Is that really accurate?

275
00:09:43,429 --> 00:09:44,517
(Is he silly or creative?)

276
00:09:44,518 --> 00:09:45,918
We can use the average.

277
00:09:45,919 --> 00:09:47,319
We can just get the average.

278
00:09:47,954 --> 00:09:48,921
It's 79cm.

279
00:09:49,222 --> 00:09:50,455
It's not over 80cm.

280
00:09:50,690 --> 00:09:52,724
- It's around 79cm.
- He barely grew.

281
00:09:52,725 --> 00:09:53,725
It's not over 80cm.

282
00:09:53,726 --> 00:09:55,127
It's 79cm.

283
00:09:55,128 --> 00:09:57,229
It's 1cm if it's 79cm.

284
00:10:01,835 --> 00:10:03,469
- It's 79cm.
- Right, 79cm.

285
00:10:03,785 --> 00:10:05,885
Yu Jun grew one centimeter!

286
00:10:05,885 --> 00:10:07,385
(Our Yu Jun has grown!)

287
00:10:08,818 --> 00:10:09,752
(Off I go.)

288
00:10:09,752 --> 00:10:11,018
Where do you want to go?

289
00:10:12,252 --> 00:10:13,952
You're extra stubborn today.

290
00:10:14,485 --> 00:10:16,218
He's going back up the stairs.

291
00:10:16,218 --> 00:10:17,252
My gosh.

292
00:10:18,152 --> 00:10:19,052
(Spotting the tape measure)

293
00:10:19,052 --> 00:10:21,185
(I'm going to measure him properly.)

294
00:10:21,952 --> 00:10:23,618
You found a tape measure?

295
00:10:23,618 --> 00:10:25,518
(Measuring his exact height)

296
00:10:25,518 --> 00:10:26,385
It's fun.

297
00:10:26,385 --> 00:10:27,885
Yes, he's right about 79cm.

298
00:10:27,885 --> 00:10:29,252
(He's done double-checking
Yu Jun's height.)

299
00:10:30,485 --> 00:10:31,785
This is your last time, okay?

300
00:10:32,418 --> 00:10:33,752
Yu Jun, you're extra stubborn today.

301
00:10:33,752 --> 00:10:36,352
Yes, extra stubborn.

302
00:10:37,052 --> 00:10:38,985
One iced Americano with mango
and one regular iced Americano.

303
00:10:38,985 --> 00:10:40,018
What would you like?

304
00:10:40,018 --> 00:10:42,718
- I want an iced Americano.
- Okay, another one.

305
00:10:42,718 --> 00:10:44,685
- And you?
- I want sweet plum tea.

306
00:10:45,318 --> 00:10:46,318
You must be tired.

307
00:10:46,685 --> 00:10:47,952
Aren't you tired now?

308
00:10:47,952 --> 00:10:48,918
Yu Jun, aren't you tired?
Even I'm tired.

309
00:10:51,785 --> 00:10:52,718
Is nobody there?

310
00:10:52,718 --> 00:10:55,718
(He loves the stairs so much
that he's even ditched his cart.)

311
00:10:55,918 --> 00:10:56,952
- Don't fall.
- Watch out.

312
00:10:56,952 --> 00:10:58,818
Let's go back.

313
00:10:58,818 --> 00:11:00,818
Let's go back to the uncles.

314
00:11:02,418 --> 00:11:04,218
I'll give it to you as a reward
if you come here.

315
00:11:04,752 --> 00:11:06,718
(You think you can use food
to make me do things?)

316
00:11:07,652 --> 00:11:09,818
(You were right.)

317
00:11:10,618 --> 00:11:11,852
I have more.

318
00:11:11,852 --> 00:11:13,618
Hold on. Help him.

319
00:11:14,718 --> 00:11:16,418
(The cameraman comes down before Yu Jun.)

320
00:11:16,818 --> 00:11:18,452
I thought you were Yu Jun.

321
00:11:18,685 --> 00:11:21,118
He only wants to climb the stairs
when he has the whole place to himself.

322
00:11:22,618 --> 00:11:23,518
Are you having fun?

323
00:11:23,518 --> 00:11:25,985
(It's a long staircase to go upstairs.)

324
00:11:25,985 --> 00:11:27,885
It must be easy for Yu Jun's parents.

325
00:11:27,885 --> 00:11:29,818
He doesn't need anything special.

326
00:11:29,818 --> 00:11:31,318
He just needs some stairs to be happy.

327
00:11:31,552 --> 00:11:33,452
(Fascinated)

328
00:11:33,452 --> 00:11:35,252
(I love stairs.)

329
00:11:35,252 --> 00:11:36,685
- Right on!
- Good boy!

330
00:11:36,685 --> 00:11:38,152
- You did it!
- We're done!

331
00:11:38,385 --> 00:11:39,252
We're done.

332
00:11:39,252 --> 00:11:40,785
Let's not go up the stairs anymore.

333
00:11:40,785 --> 00:11:42,285
My back feels like it's about to break.

334
00:11:42,785 --> 00:11:43,918
(I'm so happy.)

335
00:11:43,918 --> 00:11:44,885
He's happy now.

336
00:11:46,852 --> 00:11:48,585
How can he like stairs so much?

337
00:11:50,352 --> 00:11:51,285
Bonk!

338
00:11:56,118 --> 00:11:58,852
(Why are you going that way?)

339
00:11:58,852 --> 00:11:59,785
No, right?

340
00:12:01,118 --> 00:12:02,318
No way.

341
00:12:04,218 --> 00:12:05,485
(Let's go up the stairs again.)

342
00:12:05,485 --> 00:12:07,452
Okay, let's go.

343
00:12:08,318 --> 00:12:10,085
Let's go, Yu Jun.

344
00:12:10,952 --> 00:12:11,952
One step.

345
00:12:12,685 --> 00:12:13,785
Two steps.

346
00:12:14,585 --> 00:12:17,385
Three steps. Four steps.

347
00:12:18,152 --> 00:12:19,585
Do you want to go up more?

348
00:12:20,752 --> 00:12:22,085
Do you want to go down now?

349
00:12:23,252 --> 00:12:24,185
(I want to go up.)
You want to go up?

350
00:12:26,318 --> 00:12:27,918
(So exciting)

351
00:12:27,918 --> 00:12:29,318
This is so much fun!

352
00:12:29,885 --> 00:12:31,885
(Playing peek-a-boo with the camera)

353
00:12:33,618 --> 00:12:35,685
(I'm all the way up.)

354
00:12:36,418 --> 00:12:38,585
Please help me, cameraman.

355
00:12:42,152 --> 00:12:44,085
Yu Jun, why don't we take
the elevator down?

356
00:12:44,718 --> 00:12:46,018
Do you want to press this button?

357
00:12:46,585 --> 00:12:48,552
(Button!)

358
00:12:50,785 --> 00:12:53,052
Yu Jun, you have to go on it...

359
00:12:53,052 --> 00:12:54,685
now that you've pressed the button.

360
00:12:56,552 --> 00:12:58,118
(The elevator-waiting pose)

361
00:12:58,118 --> 00:12:59,018
Let's go, Yu Jun.

362
00:13:00,818 --> 00:13:01,685
Come on.
(I'm down now!)

363
00:13:03,752 --> 00:13:04,785
Yu Jun.

364
00:13:06,785 --> 00:13:08,418
No, Yu Jun.

365
00:13:09,418 --> 00:13:10,285
Come here.

366
00:13:11,418 --> 00:13:13,018
Yu Jun! Come here.

367
00:13:13,585 --> 00:13:15,985
(No, you need to come to me.)

368
00:13:16,618 --> 00:13:19,252
(He took the elevator,
but he's going down the stairs again.)

369
00:13:19,852 --> 00:13:22,585
Can you not lean so far forward?

370
00:13:23,418 --> 00:13:24,485
Watch out, Yu Jun.

371
00:13:24,485 --> 00:13:25,985
Please don't lean so far forward.

372
00:13:25,985 --> 00:13:26,818
Please.
Yu Jun!

373
00:13:28,418 --> 00:13:31,218
(Picking up Yu Jun)

374
00:13:31,785 --> 00:13:32,818
Okay, let's stop here.

375
00:13:32,818 --> 00:13:33,652
Come on.

376
00:13:35,018 --> 00:13:38,785
(Climbing down the stairs,
clutching BEOMGYU's hand)

377
00:13:39,052 --> 00:13:40,285
(Sighing)

378
00:13:42,118 --> 00:13:44,418
(Where are the other uncles, by the way?)

379
00:13:44,418 --> 00:13:46,085
Good job, Yu Jun!

380
00:13:47,152 --> 00:13:49,952
(Your drink is ready, sir.)

381
00:13:49,952 --> 00:13:51,052
Do you want to go into the sauna?

382
00:13:51,718 --> 00:13:52,618
Let's go.

383
00:13:53,152 --> 00:13:56,452
(SOOBIN and TAEHYUN are heading
into the extra hot sauna.)

384
00:13:57,352 --> 00:13:58,352
This is perfect.

385
00:13:58,985 --> 00:14:00,018
It's so nice.

386
00:14:00,852 --> 00:14:01,885
It's so relaxing.

387
00:14:01,885 --> 00:14:03,918
- Aren't you getting drowsy too?
- Yes.

388
00:14:03,918 --> 00:14:05,785
(YEONJUN and HUENINGKAI are enjoying
phytoncide therapy.)

389
00:14:06,518 --> 00:14:10,385
(BEOMGYU is drenched in sweat.)

390
00:14:11,852 --> 00:14:16,252
(Why is this happening to me?)

391
00:14:17,618 --> 00:14:18,485
Yu Jun.

392
00:14:19,652 --> 00:14:21,218
Oh, an elevator!

393
00:14:21,218 --> 00:14:22,018
There it is!

394
00:14:22,018 --> 00:14:24,218
(Humpback BEOMGYU)

395
00:14:25,418 --> 00:14:26,418
Here.

396
00:14:26,885 --> 00:14:27,752
Press this.

397
00:14:28,852 --> 00:14:29,685
Here.

398
00:14:31,585 --> 00:14:34,585
Help me!

399
00:14:35,752 --> 00:14:37,052
I need some help!

400
00:14:39,385 --> 00:14:40,252
Please!

401
00:14:40,685 --> 00:14:42,985
Yu Jun, what's that over there?

402
00:14:43,518 --> 00:14:45,918
(Keeping him from seeing the stairs)

403
00:14:46,818 --> 00:14:48,585
Yes, let's go that way.

404
00:14:48,585 --> 00:14:49,852
That's so cool!

405
00:14:49,852 --> 00:14:50,852
(Is he done with the stairs?)

406
00:14:52,452 --> 00:14:54,018
Okay.

407
00:14:54,018 --> 00:14:56,418
Yu Jun, what's that?

408
00:14:56,418 --> 00:14:57,518
What is that?

409
00:14:57,518 --> 00:14:58,985
Yu Jun, wait.

410
00:14:58,985 --> 00:15:00,585
Look at the puppy.

411
00:15:01,518 --> 00:15:02,452
Woof, woof!

412
00:15:04,385 --> 00:15:05,618
Just run me over with your cart.

413
00:15:06,052 --> 00:15:07,518
I'd rather have you run me over.

414
00:15:07,818 --> 00:15:08,718
No.

415
00:15:09,452 --> 00:15:10,852
(Trying to divert him)

416
00:15:10,852 --> 00:15:12,418
(Let go!)

417
00:15:15,552 --> 00:15:16,718
(Trying again)

418
00:15:16,952 --> 00:15:18,285
(I told you to let go!)

419
00:15:18,285 --> 00:15:20,418
Come on!

420
00:15:21,218 --> 00:15:22,485
I'm tired!

421
00:15:25,285 --> 00:15:27,385
(BEOMGYU is crying.)

422
00:15:27,918 --> 00:15:29,485
(Going up the stairs again)

423
00:15:30,385 --> 00:15:32,785
(I'm laughing, but I'm not.)

424
00:15:32,785 --> 00:15:33,618
Let's go.

425
00:15:34,152 --> 00:15:35,085
One, two.

426
00:15:35,885 --> 00:15:37,018
(Sighing)

427
00:15:37,252 --> 00:15:40,452
One, two.

428
00:15:40,952 --> 00:15:42,627
Where did everyone go?

429
00:15:44,418 --> 00:15:47,885
(Melting in the perfect temperature set
by nature)

430
00:15:49,885 --> 00:15:53,285
(Roasting themselves in intense heat)

431
00:15:55,852 --> 00:16:00,085
(A staircase date
hotter than the extra hot sauna)

432
00:16:03,485 --> 00:16:06,352
(Uncle BEOMGYU is the best.)

433
00:16:07,252 --> 00:16:09,152
Do you want to go up?

434
00:16:09,518 --> 00:16:10,418
No.

435
00:16:10,418 --> 00:16:11,985
You want to go down?

436
00:16:12,952 --> 00:16:15,052
(Going down the same set of stairs)

437
00:16:16,052 --> 00:16:18,885
(Climbing the same stairs again)

438
00:16:20,285 --> 00:16:24,818
(The other uncles are napping peacefully,
thanks to Uncle BEOMGYU's sacrifice.)

439
00:16:26,385 --> 00:16:28,485
(Eyes opening)

440
00:16:29,018 --> 00:16:31,752
(HUENINGKAI has suddenly woken up.)

441
00:16:33,252 --> 00:16:34,118
Where are they?

442
00:16:34,618 --> 00:16:35,552
At the stairs again?

443
00:16:36,618 --> 00:16:38,852
Go!

444
00:16:40,485 --> 00:16:42,918
(KAI has finally joined
the stair climbers.)

445
00:16:42,918 --> 00:16:44,652
BEOMGYU, where are SOOBIN and TAEHYUN?

446
00:16:45,218 --> 00:16:46,252
I don't know.

447
00:16:46,252 --> 00:16:48,518
I've climbed up and down the stairs
4 or 5 times now.

448
00:16:49,318 --> 00:16:50,485
Dad?

449
00:16:50,485 --> 00:16:52,585
(The cameraman has given up.)

450
00:16:52,852 --> 00:16:53,652
Here!

451
00:16:54,352 --> 00:16:55,518
There's an elevator.

452
00:16:56,252 --> 00:16:58,452
(They took the elevator down.)

453
00:16:58,918 --> 00:17:00,952
(Automatically heading
to the stairs again)

454
00:17:00,952 --> 00:17:02,152
The coffee is ready.

455
00:17:02,152 --> 00:17:03,252
(Successfully turning the cart)

456
00:17:03,252 --> 00:17:04,185
(I need to go!)

457
00:17:04,618 --> 00:17:05,985
(No more stairs!)

458
00:17:05,985 --> 00:17:06,885
Let's go!

459
00:17:08,218 --> 00:17:09,818
(Stairs are the best!)

460
00:17:09,818 --> 00:17:10,985
No, come on.

461
00:17:12,985 --> 00:17:14,418
You're kidding.

462
00:17:14,785 --> 00:17:15,985
We just came down.

463
00:17:17,452 --> 00:17:19,618
(But I want to go up the stairs again.)

464
00:17:19,818 --> 00:17:20,685
Why?

465
00:17:20,685 --> 00:17:22,018
- The stairs?
- What's wrong?

466
00:17:22,018 --> 00:17:23,252
He wants to go up the stairs.

467
00:17:23,252 --> 00:17:24,485
(Baby Choi is extra stubborn.)

468
00:17:25,152 --> 00:17:28,052
(SOOBIN is back from his nap,
and they're still climbing the stairs.)

469
00:17:28,052 --> 00:17:30,318
There are so many game machines there.

470
00:17:30,318 --> 00:17:31,786
How does he find stairs more interesting?

471
00:17:33,085 --> 00:17:34,052
Where did he go?

472
00:17:34,552 --> 00:17:35,518
He's climbing the stairs.

473
00:17:35,818 --> 00:17:36,785
The stairs?

474
00:17:36,785 --> 00:17:39,552
Is he having his stair time?

475
00:17:40,418 --> 00:17:41,885
What is he doing there?

476
00:17:41,885 --> 00:17:43,052
This is ridiculous.

477
00:17:43,285 --> 00:17:44,252
Why?

478
00:17:46,518 --> 00:17:47,885
I think my eyes are going crazy now...

479
00:17:47,885 --> 00:17:49,152
from staring at the stairs for so long.

480
00:17:50,018 --> 00:17:50,785
Same.

481
00:17:51,718 --> 00:17:52,885
Join us later.

482
00:17:53,385 --> 00:17:55,152
Let's go up.

483
00:17:55,618 --> 00:17:56,485
(There are still some more!)

484
00:17:56,485 --> 00:17:58,452
Okay, let's go up and down again.

485
00:17:59,552 --> 00:18:01,818
(The stair-climbing uncle has
reached his limit.)

486
00:18:04,318 --> 00:18:06,552
(What's going on?)

487
00:18:09,018 --> 00:18:10,485
Sorry, Yu Jun!

488
00:18:10,485 --> 00:18:11,418
Please give me a break!
Why? What have you done?

489
00:18:12,985 --> 00:18:16,918
(Uncle BEOMGYU's desperate cries
to escape the nightmare of stairs)

490
00:18:18,152 --> 00:18:19,952
You can't cry here, Yu Jun!

491
00:18:20,218 --> 00:18:21,685
There are too many people around!

492
00:18:22,985 --> 00:18:26,218
(I'll do anything for you,
other than going up the stairs again.)

493
00:18:28,518 --> 00:18:29,452
(Humpback BEOMGYU is back.)

494
00:18:29,452 --> 00:18:32,818
(No parent can beat their kid, after all.)

495
00:18:34,252 --> 00:18:36,852
Do you want to take some photos, Yu Jun?

496
00:18:36,852 --> 00:18:37,852
Come here.

497
00:18:38,718 --> 00:18:40,052
Ta-da!

498
00:18:40,952 --> 00:18:42,452
Do you want to take some photos?

499
00:18:43,085 --> 00:18:44,785
Do you want to press the button?

500
00:18:44,785 --> 00:18:46,152
Yu Jun can choose the frame.

501
00:18:48,318 --> 00:18:50,652
- I like that too.
- Yes.

502
00:18:50,652 --> 00:18:53,185
But I look like a mess.

503
00:18:53,685 --> 00:18:55,618
- You look good.
- Surprisingly.

504
00:18:55,618 --> 00:18:57,785
- Get in the frame.
- Okay.

505
00:18:59,118 --> 00:19:00,652
What's this?

506
00:19:01,585 --> 00:19:03,318
- I love you!
- I love you!

507
00:19:03,318 --> 00:19:04,718
Yu Jun is making a heart!

508
00:19:05,085 --> 00:19:06,685
- I love you!
- I love you!

509
00:19:08,118 --> 00:19:09,018
Wait!

510
00:19:10,052 --> 00:19:11,405
He stretched his arm in the last minute.

511
00:19:11,552 --> 00:19:12,485
Should we wink?

512
00:19:12,485 --> 00:19:13,785
- Okay, wink!
- Wink!

513
00:19:14,752 --> 00:19:16,218
- Wink, Yu Jun!
- Wink!

514
00:19:16,218 --> 00:19:17,552
Right on!

515
00:19:19,085 --> 00:19:20,018
That looks so cute.

516
00:19:20,385 --> 00:19:21,318
Are you hot, Yu Jun?

517
00:19:22,718 --> 00:19:24,285
(The photos are ready.)

518
00:19:24,285 --> 00:19:25,118
This is for you, Yu Jun!

519
00:19:26,952 --> 00:19:28,118
Don't tear it, okay?

520
00:19:50,552 --> 00:19:52,785
(Waddling)

521
00:19:53,018 --> 00:19:57,185
(Entering with Uncle YEONJUN's escort)

522
00:19:58,018 --> 00:19:59,252
It's so spacious.

523
00:19:59,253 --> 00:20:01,440
- What is this place?
- There's a clothing store.

524
00:20:01,474 --> 00:20:02,361
It's huge.

525
00:20:02,362 --> 00:20:03,602
(Cafe time to recharge)

526
00:20:03,883 --> 00:20:04,916
Isn't it, Yu Jun?

527
00:20:05,658 --> 00:20:06,849
- Can I get a kiss?
- Snacks!

528
00:20:06,916 --> 00:20:07,949
- Snacks.
- Snacks.

529
00:20:08,449 --> 00:20:10,049
He just wants snacks.

530
00:20:10,316 --> 00:20:11,316
Snacks!
Can't you say, "Bro?"

531
00:20:12,583 --> 00:20:14,716
You say "Mommy," "snacks," and "bonk,"
but not "Bro?"

532
00:20:14,983 --> 00:20:15,983
Bonk!

533
00:20:15,983 --> 00:20:17,616
(Bonk, not bro!)

534
00:20:17,616 --> 00:20:20,249
(Uncles' hearts melt
from a single "Bonk.")

535
00:20:20,249 --> 00:20:21,949
- Bro!
- Bonk!

536
00:20:21,949 --> 00:20:22,949
Bro!

537
00:20:23,016 --> 00:20:24,316
(Playing "Bonk" is his favorite.)

538
